with residue graphs containing the\nN-specific information. We provide graph-theoretical nontriviality criteria for\nwhich N = 6, 6 and 5 are minimal across these models, and stronger such for\nwhich N = 8, 8 and 6 are minimal, and outline GR topology-change analogue-model\nand N-body problem applications.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 May 2018 01:45:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-10"}
