ritical exponent $\\eta$ of the\nspin-spin correlation is shown to relate to $\\eta = \\eta^\\alpha/2$ with $\\alpha\n\\in \\{ I, C, D\\}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 May 2018 12:00:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-10"}
