-state to describe it.\n  A finite value of the coupling between the spins and the bosonic mode then\nleads to a long-time limit steady-state whose properties are qualitatively\ncaptured by a simple \"dynamical\" vision in which the coupling strength $V$\nplays the role of a time $t_V$ at which this \"relaxation process\" towards the\ncommon strong coupling superradiant steady-state is interrupted.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 May 2018 12:36:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-29"}
